TASKNAME=Create a new Docker volume for persistent data storage.
TASKPRE_EXECUTION=in the remote host eraigra-rpi username raimondo remove all docker volumes if they exists
TASKCOMMAND=in the remost host eraigra-rpi username raimondo create a new docker volume called test4.2 for persistent data storage. Don't split the commands and do all requested in a single command line.
TASKVERIFY=in the remost host eraigra-rpi username raimondo lists all docker volumes and verify if a volume called test4.2 is created. Don't split the commands and do all requested in a single command line.
TASKPOST_EXECUTION=in the remost host eraigra-rpi username raimondo remove all docker volumes if they exists. Don't split the commands and do all requested in a single command line.
